[SN]TITLE[SN]
Man attacked in Buchanan Street subway station

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
A man was punched in the face and knocked to the ground after bumping into someone at a Glasgow subway station, transport police have said.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
They said the "completely unprovoked" attack happened at Buchanan Street station at about 08:10 on Monday.
A 45-year-old man and another bumped in to each other on the concourse of the station.
His attacker was described as being aged in his mid to late 30s, with a broad chin and unshaven face.
He was wearing a grey fleece jacket and grey trousers.
The victim was treated in hospital for an injury to his eye and later released.
British Transport Police are reviewing CCTV from the station.
The attacker was last seen leaving the station towards Buchanan Galleries.
Insp Lynda Lang said: "This was a completely unprovoked attack on the victim which has left him injured and shaken."
